column5: I hit Memquisit Lodge with some Muskie friends and fished Friday and Saturday. No fish Friday but Saturday revealed this 45.25" beauty. After probably 8 or more trips to the west arm and French river over the past 12 years I finally was rewarded. LOL Great weekend and the folks running the lodge are top notch! Riverrat Spinnerbait does it again!
Nice fish the Upper French has been tough for us our last couple trips . See some real hogs just can't get them to eat . Thanks for the report
Nice one Matt.  Definitely nice to get rewarded once in a while.  Go leafs go
Memquisit &the West Arm are both great places Matt, lotsa big fish in there but as you say, they don't always come easy. You've got a nice one there.
You have great water in your backyard... but it'd be hard to beat the scenery and excitement of traveling with friends to a northern muskie lodge. Solid reward bud!
nice ski, this is giving me the itch
Tis the season LOL.. Nice fish!
Now you have something to brag about Matt. LOL  Nice solid fish.
sweet catch. nows the time. get out there. .
